        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-04T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-04T23:00:00-05:00" n="998" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d998">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.014/2–546: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-05T11:00:00+07:00">February 5, 1946—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 5—10:24 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>221. Aerial survey of China by War Dept (Emb 157, Jan 25). Note from FonOff dated
                    Jan 29 states that in the case of Sinkiang aerial photography proposed to be
                    undertaken by War Dept is still to be held in abeyance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
